Community Health Systems, Inc. (CHS) is a provider of general hospital healthcare services in the United States. Its services include orthopedics, cardiology, occupational medicine, diagnostic services, emergency services, rehabilitation treatment, home health services, and skilled nursing services. The company operates… MoreCommunity Health Systems, Inc. (CHS) is a provider of general hospital healthcare services in the United States. Its services include orthopedics, cardiology, occupational medicine, diagnostic services, emergency services, rehabilitation treatment, home health services, and skilled nursing services. The company operates approximately 160 hospitals in the country, with approximately 27,000 beds.  It also owns imaging centers, home health agencies, and ambulatory surgery centers.

CHS completed its acquisition of Health Management Associates in early 2014.  In April 2016, the CHS spun off Quorum Health Corporation, combining Quorum Health Resources LLC and 38 hospitals formerly owned by CHS.

CHS is selling Rockwood Health System to MultiCare.  The deal is slated to close in early 2017.  CHS Sold Yakima Regional Medical Center, and Toppenish Community Hospital to Sunnyside Community Hospital in 2017. CHS is in the process of selling 8 hospitals to Steward Health are, the deal is expected to close in late 2017.
