CHS/Community Health Systems, Inc. Key Developments

CHS/Community Health Systems, Inc. Announces Pricing of Upsized Tack-On Offering of $900,000,000 of 6.250% Senior Secured Notes Due 2023
May 9 17
Community Health Systems, Inc. announced that its wholly owned subsidiary CHS/Community Health Systems, Inc. has priced a tack-on offering of $900,000,000 aggregate principal amount of its 6.250% Senior Secured Notes due 2023 at an issue price of 101.75% of their aggregate principal amount plus accrued interest from March 16, 2017. The size of the offering was increased by $200,000,000 aggregate principal amount subsequent to the initial announcement of the offering. The sale of the Additional Notes is expected to be consummated on or about May 12, 2017, subject to customary closing conditions. The offering is being made by means of an underwritten public offering pursuant to an automatic shelf registration statement filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The company intends to use the net proceeds of the offering to prepay and extinguish the company's Term A Facility, to pay related fees and expenses and for general corporate purposes, which may include the repayment of secured debt.


